Preheat your oven to 200°C. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and
seeds. Slice into thin strips. Halve and peel the @red onion{1}. Chop each half
into 4-5 wedges.

Pop the pepper, onion and @British chicken thighs{3} on a large #baking tray{}.
Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat and make
sure the chicken thighs are flat.

> TIP: Use 2 baking trays if cooking for 3 or 4 people.

Roast on the middle shelf of your oven until the chicken is cooked through and
the veg is soft, ~{16-18%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling chicken and its packaging.
> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Pop the @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}, @tomato puree{30%g} and half the
@BBQ sauce{64%g} in a large #bowl{}. Add the @water{1%tbsp} and mix together.
Set aside. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g} and @Monterey Jack cheese{30%g}.

Once the chicken and veg are cooked, remove from the oven. Pop the veg into the
bowl with the sauce. Pull the chicken apart into strips using 2 #forks{}. Add
the chicken to the sauce and mix together to combine.

Turn your oven up to 220°C. Pop your @plain naans{2} on your #baking tray{}
(no need to wash). Divide your remaining BBQ sauce between the naans and use a
#spoon{} to spread it out until you have approximately a 1cm border. Divide the
BBQ chicken mixture between the naans and sprinkle over the cheese. Bake in
your oven until the cheese has melted, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Serve the BBQ chicken naanizzas on #plates{}. Enjoy!